{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-04558/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-04558"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:45:58"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["plan américain"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["high"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["two shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A man and woman lay together in bed as they hold each other."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04558/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-04558","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04558/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-04558"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04558/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04558/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04558/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04558/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04558/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04558/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04558/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04558/canvas/1/3d0fa5f5-ce2e-40b5-9031-761d3ac9bea0","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T18:34:59.847Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>PTA has stated that, despite the presence and stature of Daniel Day-Lewis, his idea was always that “we had a film that belonged to the girl. It was her story.” According to the director, after two weeks the actor confessed to him that Vicky Krieps makes him “nervous” (Xixax TV, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW101213715 BCX0\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=f3It380DGqk\"><u>PHANTOM THREAD - AUDIO - Paul Thomas Anderson in conversation with Alan Parker</u></a>”).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04558/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:765.4078194239291,453.207163958641,358.332025480059,202.92997599704586"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04558/canvas/1/546f646f-c310-4cf3-98cb-6f612c497e4a","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T18:35:22.048Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The green book on Reynolds’s bedside is a copy of the London Magazine, a periodical.&nbsp; Based on what we can see in the screenshot, it is most likely no. 6, which came out in July 1954. This volume features “A Cottage in Cornwall” by C.H.B. Kitchin, a short story about a woman who is institutionalized because she is convinced her husband is poisoning her. The inclusion of the edition featuring this specific story is likely a nod to the events of the film, as not long after this scene Alma <em>will </em>poison Reynolds.</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04558/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:31.96847304283594,861.5161096750369,193.36456794682422,94.11489106351553"}}}]}]}]}